summary: This is an email chain between US Attorney's Office (SDNY) prosecutors discussing case updates, including a meeting in California that did not yield significant new information, the inability to bring an enticement charge, and scheduling a proffer session with a witness (M) for background information.

persons.name: Maurene
persons.context: Mentioned as having a scheduling conflict due to being in White Plains, suggesting involvement in the case from the prosecution side.

connections.description: Both are involved in the legal proceedings, with Maurene as a prosecutor and M as a witness/subject providing a proffer.

events.title: Meeting in California
events.description: A meeting took place in California that did not add significant information, and it was determined an enticement charge could not be brought due to timing/location facts.

events.title: Scheduled proffer session with M
events.description: M is scheduled to come in for a limited proffer to talk about her background.

keyFacts: A meeting in California did not yield significant new information for the case.
Prosecutors determined they almost certainly could not bring an enticement charge based on timing and location facts.
Witness M is scheduled for a limited proffer session to discuss her background.
M is still unsure about pursuing a criminal case, with further discussions planned with her attorneys.
The email chain shows internal prosecution coordination and scheduling efforts within the US Attorney's Office (SDNY).
